        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(agents): scope session-history guard to latest-user-answered",
        "body": "Fixes #69086.\n\n## Summary\n- scope the session-history guard to assistant messages that occur after the latest user message\n- preserve Claude CLI transcript support for `type: assistant` / `type: user` JSONL records as well as OpenClaw `type: message` records\n- add a regression fixture where an earlier assistant response is followed by a fresh unanswered user message\n\n## Test\n- `pnpm test src/agents/command/attempt-execution.test.ts` — 35/35 passed\n\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nUpdated 2026-05-29 from a real macOS/OpenClaw checkout after Dallin Romney's rebase notice.\n\n- Rebasing the PR branch onto current `openclaw/openclaw:main` succeeded cleanly.\n- Current `main` still returns true on the first assistant record in the inspected transcript, so the guard bug is still present upstream.\n- The PR now inspects the transcript tail rather than the first 500 records, so a fresh unanswered user turn after the old scan cap does not get misclassified as answered.\n- Focused local verification passed on the rebased branch:\n  - `pnpm test src/agents/command/attempt-execution.test.ts` → 36/36 passed\n  - `pnpm exec oxfmt --check --threads=1 src/agents/command/attempt-execution.helpers.ts src/agents/command/attempt-execution.test.ts` → passed\n- The broader command `node scripts/crabbox-wrapper.mjs run --shell -- \"pnpm check:changed\"` did not reach code checks locally because this host's `crabbox` binary failed its own `--version/--help` sanity check (`selected binary failed basic --version/--help sanity checks`).\n\nThe added regression is the concrete after-fix proof for the prior review finding: an old user→assistant turn, 501 filler records, then a fresh unanswered user turn now returns `false`.\n",
        "branch": "fix/attempt-execution-session-guard-69086",
